      "It was a grey Tuesday in October 2019 when <em>Eleanor first spotted James</em> across a crowded coffee shop in Notting Hill. He was reading the wrong Murakami — she couldn't help herself.",
      "What began as a gentle correction became a two-hour conversation, which became a walk through Holland Park, which became dinner, which became everything.",
      "They discovered a shared love of <em>early mornings, slow Sundays</em>, and arguing about who makes better scrambled eggs. (It's Eleanor. James still insists otherwise.)",
      "In the summer of 2022, James proposed on a wooden bridge in the Cotswolds — the very spot where they'd spent their first weekend away. Eleanor said yes before he'd finished asking.",
      "<em>Thank you for being part of this day.</em>"
